   <text>
      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Mornington Hotel ¶ Snapper Point ¶ 13 Feby 1860 ¶ Dr Mueller M.D. &amp;c ¶ Exploration Committee...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">60.02.13a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Harley Goodall</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS 13071 Royal Society of Victoria Exploration Committee records, box 2077/3, La Trobe Australian Manuscripts Collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Mornington Hotel</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Snapper Point</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">13 Feby 1860</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr Mueller M.D. &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Exploration Committee</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The accompanying letter of Mr Simon Sahner<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">S. Sahner to M, 13 February 1860.</p>
               </note> needs no comment from me further than that I have much pleasure in testifying to his uniform steadiness industry sobriety &amp; good character. I have known him ever since I have been resident here — he has a good constitution, is a thorough good axe man &amp; a a<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">a </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">repeated</seg>
                     <seg style="">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> sure marksman, understands horses &amp; is an experienced intelligent bushman. As far as my judgement goes he is just the man I should consider particularly fitted to make one of an exploring party<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. the party being put together for what became known as the Burke &amp; Wills Exploring Expedition, 1860-1. Sahner was not appointed to the Expedition party; see list of expedition members selected by Robert O'Hara Burke in M <seg style="font-style: italic; ">et al.</seg> to the Royal Society of Victoria, December 1860 (in this edition as 60-12-00).</p>
               </note> &amp; as such I most <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">conscientiously</hi>
               </seg> recommend him to the notice of yourself &amp; the committee</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Harley Goodall</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">PS</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">There is one point which I have not alluded to which I think will strongly recommend him to the Committee — he is an intelligent educated man yet willing &amp; <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">thoro'ly capable</hi>
               </seg> of taking a subordinate position.</p>
         </div>
